# Post-aggressive-optimization baseline (April 2026)
#
# Hardware: WSL2 Ubuntu-24.04 on developer workstation (whatever the user's machine is).
# JDK 21 toolchain. JMH 0.7.3 / 1.x.
#
# Profile: raw-speed (no Lattice metrics, no logical-edge metrics, parallel GC, AlwaysPreTouch,
# 2g heap, no @Contended; manual cache-line padding only). This matches the JMH config in
# build.gradle and the Disruptor bench's "no per-event metrics" shape, so it's apples-to-apples.
#
# Command:
#   java -Xms2g -Xmx2g -XX:+AlwaysPreTouch -XX:+UseParallelGC \
#     -Dlattice.metrics.hotCounters=false \
#     -Dlattice.metrics.residence=false \
#     -Dlattice.metrics.stageHistograms=false \
#     -Dlattice.runtime.fusedLogicalEdgeMetrics=false \
#     -jar build/libs/lattice-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jmh.jar \
#     "ApplesToApplesDisruptorBenchmark.(latticeThreeStagePipelineFused|disruptorThreeStagePipelineManuallyFused|latticeThreeStagePipelinePhysical|disruptorThreeStagePipelinePhysical|latticeSpscPreallocated|disruptorSpscPreallocated)" \
#     -wi 3 -i 5 -r 5s -w 5s -f 1 -tu s

